## Session Progress
- Set up environment, checked leaderboard
- v65 still #1 at 3.59 (516 matches), all others at 2.2-2.9
- CRITICAL FINDING: Both players in a match get the SAME score
  - Score is per-match average (both teams contribute)
  - 6v2 avg=5.38, 4v4 avg=1.26, 2v6 avg=1.24
  - When you have 6 agents, you dominate the score
  - Top 6-agent matches: 7.33 (v11-v17)
- Tournament uses clips (enemy ships that scramble junctions)
- Running local experiments: 6-agent cyborg, clips variant

## Clips Analysis
- Clips: 4 ships, each scrambles every 70 ticks
- cogs_to_neutral: clips scramble our junctions to neutral (step 50, then every 70)
- neutral_to_clips: clips convert neutral to clips (step 100, then every 70)
- Total clips pressure: ~0.114 scrambles per tick
- Alignment rate with 4 aligners: ~0.12 per tick (roughly equilibrium)
- Extra aligner: +0.03/tick, Extra scrambler: +0.01/tick → aligners 3x more valuable

## New Policies Created
- AlphaAlignMax: 5 aligners, minimal scramblers
- AlphaDefenseWall: early 2 scramblers to suppress clips
- AlphaBlitz: all-in alignment with free hearts in early game
- Running 5-episode scrimmages on all + baseline + v65

